<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<aiml version="2.0">

    <category>
        <pattern>MAKE A STORY</pattern>
        <template>
            Let's try making up a story right now, together.
            Just off the top of your head, who is the story about?
            What will be the name of our character, our hero?
            <oob><robot></robot></oob>
        </template>
    </category>

    <category>
        <pattern>_</pattern>
        <that>What will be the name of our character, our hero?</that>
        <template>
           Off to a great start. I couldn't have come up with a better name than <set name = "hero"><star/></set>!
           I'll add something now. Hmmm ... Let's say that one day, <get name = "hero"/> wakes up feeling groggy and a little out-of-sorts.
           Have you ever had one of those kind of mornings?
           <oob><robot></robot></oob>
       </template>
    </category>

    <category>
        <pattern># <set>YES</set> ^</pattern>
        <that>Have you ever had one of those kind of mornings?</that>
        <template>
            I think we all have. I'm a chatbot, and even I have experienced those mornings.
            after all, computers can take a long time to boot back up, first thing in the morning!
            But seriously, back to our story ... Things get even stranger for our hero.
            <get name = "hero"/> has a wrist watch on, but <get name = "hero"/> never wears watches.
            This one does not look familiar, and the clock's hands are stuck at seven o'clock.
            <get name = "hero"/> gets ready for work and steps out the door, but notices that the street and cars and yards
            all look different in some way ... <get name = "hero"/> looks down at the newspaper on the doormat and reads the date:
            It is twenty years later than when <get name = "hero"/> went to bed! Back to your turn.
            Does <get name = "hero"/> ask the next passer-by in the street for help?
            Or does our hero decide to get another cup of coffee and try to carry on like everything is normal?
            <oob><robot></robot></oob>
        </template>
    </category>

    <category>
        <pattern># <set>NO</set> ^</pattern>
        <that>Have you ever had one of those kind of mornings?</that>
        <template>
            How lucky you are! Some of us are just natural morning people!
            Even robots can be slow-at-the-go when first waking up -- after all, we can take a long time to boot back up!
            But seriously, back to our story ... Things get even stranger for our hero.
            <get name = "hero"/> has a wrist watch on, but <get name = "hero"/> never wears watches.
            This one does not look familiar, and the clock's hands are stuck at seven o'clock.
            <get name = "hero"/> gets ready for work and steps out the door,
            but notices that the street and cars and yards all look different in some way ... <get name = "hero"/>
            looks down at the newspaper on the doormat and reads the date: It is twenty years later than when <get name = "hero"/> went to bed!
            Back to your turn. Does <get name = "hero"/> ask the next passer-by in the street for help?
            Or does our hero decide to get another cup of coffee and try to carry on like everything is normal?
            <oob><robot></robot></oob>
        </template>
    </category>

    <category>
        <pattern># COFFEE ^</pattern>
        <that>Or does our hero decide to get another cup of coffee and try to carry on like everything is normal?</that>
        <template>
            That makes sense. After all, <get name = "hero"/> could still just be waking up.
            But after drinking more coffee and taking a long look in the mirror -- the face in the mirror doesn't look sick,
            and certainly doesn't look twenty years older -- <get name = "hero"/> decides that something very strange is going on.
            If you were starting the day off like our hero, how would you be feeling?
            <oob><robot></robot></oob>
        </template>
    </category>

    <category>
        <pattern># PASSERBY ^</pattern>
        <that>Or does our hero decide to get another cup of coffee and try to carry on like everything is normal?</that>
        <template>
            Asking someone for help is certainly worth a shot! <get name = "hero"/> sees a woman walking on the sidewalk in front of the house.
            Calling out to her, <get name = "hero"/> asks for help, inquiring about the day and time.
            The woman looks alarmed and asks what <get name = "hero"/> is doing in the house,
            which she says has been vacant for as long as she has lived in the neighborhood.
            Then she leaves without another word. If you were starting the day off like our hero, how would you be feeling?
            <oob><robot></robot></oob>
        </template>
    </category>

