    <category>
        <pattern># DECIDES ^</pattern>
        <that>hoping that all of this is a weird dream?</that>
        <template>
            Good thinking. <get name = "hero"/> has to figure out what the heck is going on, and Robert might be able to help.
            When <get name = "hero"/> knocks on his door, Robert greets him with a cry of exclamation.
            The man is astonished to see <get name = "hero"/> all these years after disappearing into thin air.
            "I am so sorry ... I did not get all the kinks worked out of that time machine before we tested it," Robert says remorsefully,
            staring at the watch-like apparatus on <get name = "hero"/>'s wrist.
            Is <get name = "hero"/> upset with Robert for allowing the time machine to be used before it was ready.
            Or is our hero relieved to finally know the truth?
            <oob><robot></robot></oob>
        </template>
    </category>

    <category>
        <pattern># GOES ^</pattern>
        <that>hoping that all of this is a weird dream?</that>
        <template>
            With the world seemingly turned upside-down, I would want to go into my computer SLEEP mode.
            <get name = "hero"/> goes back to bed, but shortly thereafter is awoken by a knock on the door.
            It is Robert, who is amazed to see <get name = "hero"/> once more. "After all these years," he says.
            A woman from the neighborhood informed Robert that a stranger was lurking around the vacant house on the street.
            Robert wanted to stop any intrusion on his old friend's property. He is astonished to see <get name = "hero"/>.
            "I am so sorry ... I did not get all the kinks worked out of that time machine before we tested it,"
            Robert says remorsefully, staring at the watch-like apparatus on <get name = "hero"/>'s wrist.
            Is <get name = "hero"/> upset with Robert for allowing the time machine to be used before it was ready.
            or is our hero relieved to finally know the truth?
            <oob><robot></robot></oob>
        </template>
    </category>

    <category>
        <pattern># UPSET ^</pattern>
        <that>or is our hero relieved to finally know the truth?</that>
        <template>
            The two friends talk, and <get name = "hero"/> finally remembers their ideas, their plans,
            and their dreams of seeing the dinosaurs, witnessing the battles of the Revolutionary War,
            observing themselves playing as children, and of course seeing what the future would hold.
            <get name = "hero"/> remembers how they had tested the time machine, but how something had gone wrong when the machine froze.
            <get name = "hero"/> had been lost in time. Exhausted from the strain of time travel,
            <get name = "hero"/> collapsed after reappearing in the bedroom of the house.
            <get name = "hero"/> expresses frustration at all those wasted years because of Robert's mistake,
            but the friends make up with one another. Robert apologizes, offering to fix the machine and allow <get name = "hero"/>
            to use it once more. Should <get name = "hero"/> use the time machine after it is fixed.
            or has our hero had enough time travel for one lifetime?
            <oob><robot></robot></oob>
        </template>
    </category>

